  <div class="topic">The Sending of Elijah</div>
  <p class="std">What shall I talk about to-day? I know what Brother Cahoon wants me to speak about. He wants
  me to speak about the coming of Elijah<span class="footRef">2</span> in the last days. I can see it in his eye. I will speak upon that
  subject then.</p>
  <p class="std">The Bible says, &ldquo;I will send you Elijah the Prophet before the coming of the great and dreadful
  day of the Lord; and he shall turn the heart of the fathers to the children, and the heart of the children
  to the fathers, lest I come and smite the earth with a curse.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">3</span></p>
  <p class="std">Now, the word <i>turn</i> here should be translated <i>bind,</i> or <i>seal.</i><span class="footRef">4</span> But what is the object of this
  important mission? or how is it to be fulfilled? The keys are to be delivered,<span class="footRef">5</span> the spirit of Elijah is
  to come,<span class="footRef">6</span> the Gospel to be established,<span class="footRef">7</span> the Saints of God gathered,<span class="footRef">8</span> Zion built up,<span class="footRef">9</span> and the Saints
  to come up as saviors on Mount Zion.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <p class="std">But how are they to become saviors<span class="footRef">11</span> on Mount Zion? By building their temples, erecting their
  baptismal fonts,<span class="footRef">12</span> and going forth and receiving all the ordinances, baptisms, confirmations,
  washings, anointings, ordinations<span class="footRef">13</span> and sealing powers<span class="footRef">14</span> upon their heads,<span class="footRef">15</span> in behalf of all their
  progenitors who are dead, and redeem them<span class="footRef">16</span> that they may come forth in the first resurrection<span class="footRef">17</span> and
  be exalted to thrones<span class="footRef">18</span> of glory<span class="footRef">19</span> with them; and herein is the chain that binds the hearts of the
  fathers to the children,<span class="footRef">20</span> and the children to the fathers,<span class="footRef">21</span> which fulfills the mission of Elijah. And
  I would to God that this temple was now done, that we might go into it, and go to work and improve
  our time,<span class="footRef">22</span> and make use of the seals while they are on earth.</p>
  <div class="topic">Saints Have Not Much Time</div>
  <p class="std">The Saints have not too much time to save and redeem their dead,<span class="footRef">23</span> and gather together their
  living relatives, that they may be saved also, before the earth will be smitten,<span class="footRef">24</span> and the consumption
  decreed<span class="footRef">25</span> falls upon the world.</p>
  <p class="std">I would advise all the Saints to go with their might<span class="footRef">26</span> and gather together all their living relatives
  to this place, that they may be sealed and saved, that they may be prepared against the day that the
  destroying angel<span class="footRef">27</span> goes forth; and if the whole</p>
